  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What problems would you like Uber to solve for you with their app?",
  "response": "As a digital assistant, I don't have personal experiences or needs, but I can suggest some common issues and improvements that users might want Uber to address in their app:\n\n1. **Enhanced Safety Features**: Users often express concerns about safety. Uber could introduce more robust safety features like real-time ID verification for both riders and drivers, emergency buttons that connect directly to local authorities, and more detailed background checks.\n\n2. **Improved Pricing Transparency**: Sometimes, surge pricing can be confusing and frustrating for users. Uber could enhance the app to provide clearer explanations of surge pricing, perhaps with visual aids showing demand and supply in real-time.\n\n3. **Better Accessibility Options**: For users with disabilities, features like wheelchair-accessible vehicle options, audio assistance for the visually impaired, and more straightforward interfaces could significantly enhance the user experience.\n\n4. **Enhanced Route Customization**: Allowing users to customize their routes more easily could be beneficial, especially for those who need to make multiple stops or prefer specific paths.\n\n5. **Integration with Public Transit**: An integrated feature that combines Uber rides with public transportation schedules could offer a more seamless travel experience, helping users plan their trips more efficiently.\n\n6. **More Personalized Services**: Options to save preferred drivers or vehicle types, set up regular rides, or customize in-app preferences could enhance user satisfaction.\n\n7. **Environmental Impact Tracking**: For eco-conscious users, features that track and display the environmental impact of their rides (like CO2 emissions) and suggest greener options could be valuable.\n\n8. **Offline Functionality**: The ability to book rides when internet connectivity is poor or non-existent could be a significant improvement, especially in rural areas or during travel abroad.\n\n9. **Enhanced Customer Support**: An in-app chat feature for real-time support, or quicker response times for issues and complaints, could improve the user experience.\n\n10. **Multi-Language Support**: Expanding language options within the app could make it more accessible to a global user base.\n\nThese suggestions reflect common user feedback and could help Uber improve their service and app functionality.",
